flowEntityConfigSwitchCommand.name: flowEntityConfigSwitchCommand
flowEntityConfigSwitchCommand.description: Protection Switch commands: Manual, Lock or Release. The 'Manual Switch' switches manually from addressed facility to the partner but does not force the traffic onto a broken fiber and it does not block the subsequent automatic functioning of the switch. The 'Lock Switch' - ask Gerald for description....... The 'Release Switch' releases the current switch command. Relevant especially to 'Lock Switch' command. For 'Manual Switch' relevant only if revertivity is supported.

flowEntityConfigInhibitSwitchToProt.name: flowEntityConfigInhibitSwitchToProt

flowEntityConfigInhibitSwitchToWork.name: flowEntityConfigInhibitSwitchToWork
flowEntityConfigInhibitSwitchToWork.description: Inhibit Switch To Working. Inhibition blocks a switch to the WKG facility (working path). Applicable for the PROTN facility in ACT state.
